                    <span>I have read a ton of history books over the course of my undergraduate and now graduate life, and this book if one of my favorite.  It is so easy to read, understand, and flows wonderfully.  I really don't like footnotes versus endnotes, but aside from that I could barely put it down.  I would highly recommend this book to any history buff, or anyone interested in the origins of slavery in America.  Jordan does an excellent job.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Excellent Book!</div>
